The paper discusses the use of multiple antennas to improve the efficiency of wireless communication systems, which falls under the field of information theory (cs.IT). It also involves the use of networked systems (cs.NI) and control systems (cs.SY) to optimize the performance of the communication system. The paper also discusses the use of multiple-input multiple-output (MIMO) systems (cs.MM) and the tradeoff between energy and spectral efficiency, which is relevant to communication systems (cs.COM).
